<i>[Memory of Encaustic Tile]</i>

33
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:09,600
<i>[Adapted from Beifeng Sanbaili's original novel "Memory of Encaustic Tile"]</i>

34
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:12,200
<i>[Episode 11]
[A Gift from the Prince]</i>

35
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:20,200
Once upon a time, a beautiful princess fell seriously ill.

36
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:23,700
Two warriors who love the princess embarked on a journey

37
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:25,800
to find a cure for the princess's illness.

38
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:31,100
They are going to find the legendary jasmine flower that can bring people back to life.

39
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:33,100
The outfit is a nice touch.
<i>[Mr. Chen, Ms. Miao, Ms. Zhao]</i>

40
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:37,200
They finally came to the place where the jasmine grew.

41
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:41,800
But they both wanted to be the princess's one and only.

42
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:49,300
So they wanted to have a final showdown with each other.

43
00:02:49,300 --> 00:02:50,700
You!

44
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:53,600
What?

45
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,800
You don't deserve her!

46
00:03:03,300 --> 00:03:04,400
I...

47
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,600
Why don't I deserve her?

48
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,800
Because I said so!

49
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,600
The actors phoned in their performances.

50
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:15,900
What's with the actors? Just a bunch of amateurs.

51
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:21,400
You can take over. I'm leaving.

52
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,500
Come back here!

53
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,200
You got the line wrong.

54
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:27,600
I forgot my next line. Just continue.

55
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:36,000
While the two princes were arguing, the dragon guarding the jasmine

56
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,600
came down from the sky

57
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:41,900
and spewed blazing flames.

58
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:57,200
The two princes buried the hatchet

59
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:03,100
and worked together to defeat the dragon.

60
00:04:10,200 --> 00:04:14,400
They worked together to defeat the dragon!

61
00:04:20,400 --> 00:04:26,000
But a warrior tragically died.

62
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,600
You shouldn't be dead. I'm the one who should die.

63
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,700
- I thought I was the one who died?
- It's me.

64
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,600
Why are you both on the floor?

65
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:42,400
One of you has to get up.

66
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,400
One of you has to get up! Just one!

67
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,000
The warrior returned with the jasmine flowers

68
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,400
and presented it to the princess.

69
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:00,500
Princess? Princess?

70
00:05:03,390 --> 00:05:06,000
What an ordinary-looking princess.

71
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:07,800
She's totally not worth dying for.

72
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,000
That's right.

73
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:13,000
Return home and present it to the princess.

74
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,800
Princess.

75
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:28,500
The princess was terribly saddened

76
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,800
when she heard that a warrior had died for her

77
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:35,000
as it suddenly dawned on her that the dead warrior

78
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,000
was the love of her life.

79
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:45,000
So the princess decided to revive the warrior with her singing.

80
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,200
Sing.

81
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:00,200
It's your turn.

82
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,600
Sing.

83
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:05,900
One, two, three, go.

84
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,500
Is this princess a mute? Why isn't she talking?

85
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:18,700
- Get off the stage!
<i>- Get off the stage!</i>

86
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:21,400
Why is she running away?

87
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:23,400
She left without saying a word.

88
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,500
What kind of stage play is this?

89
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,300
Pull the curtains!

90
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:31,000
These kids aren't up for it.

91
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,900
They should just focus on studying. This isn't for them.

92
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,700
Pull the curtains!

93
00:06:34,700 --> 00:06:37,200
I haven't gotten inside yet!

94
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,400
Tang Ya.

95
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:07,000
Are you all right?

96
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,700
I'm fine.

97
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,700
Where are Xue and the others?

98
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:18,000
They went to talk to the teachers.

99
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,500
It's all my fault.

100
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,000
I suffered from stage fright again.

101
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:24,700
I've let you guys down.

102
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:27,600
You are still better than Zhang Qi and Sunian.

103
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:30,000
They didn't even remember their lines.

104
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
What's the point of me remembering the lines?

105
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,800
I couldn't even utter a word out.

106
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,800
I watched you rehearse.

107
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:40,900
Just perform like you normally did, and you'd do great.

108
00:07:40,900 --> 00:07:43,000
I was too nervous being on the stage.

109
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,000
I ruined it all for you guys.

110
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,800
I know you don't want to hurt my feelings.

111
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:51,800
Maybe I should just quit?

112
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,800
Don't say that.

113
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:58,300
Tang Ya, trust me. Give it another try.

114
00:07:58,300 --> 00:08:00,500
We've got your back.

115
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:03,400
I'm afraid I might let you down.

116
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,000
Tang Ya.

117
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,800
Actually, I myself am not a confident person.

118
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:14,700
But I'm trying to overcome it.

119
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:17,400
You're way better than me.

120
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:21,000
So don't doubt yourself. Okay?

121
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,800
All right. Enough crying.

122
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:31,500
Let's go and find Xue.

123
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:33,000
Come on.

124
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:37,000
Come on!

125
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:52,000
Let's go.

126
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:58,400
Ms. Miao, we didn't have time to rehearse properly.

127
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,700
Could you give us another chance to try it out?

128
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,400
Hear me out.

129
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:07,300
Zheng Sunian. The top Grade 12 student.

130
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:10,800
Zhang Qi. You're from the competition class, right?

131
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:13,400
Both of you are doing great in your studies.

132
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,400
So just focus on your studies.

133
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,400
Don't bother taking part in anything else.

134
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:19,000
Give us another chance.

135
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,700
Just one more chance.

136
00:09:20,700 --> 00:09:23,300
Coming up next is the drama troupe's performance.

137
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:25,600
Why don't we watch other stage plays first?

138
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:27,500
You can come back to me again after that.

139
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:28,800
Ms. Miao.

140
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,000
Off you go now.

141
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:38,200
Five, six, seven, eight. Move.

142
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,200
One, two, down.

143
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:45,400
[Dance in youth's rhythm, let brilliance bloom]
Three, four, five, six, seven, eight, slow down.

144
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:53,200
Two, two, three, four, five, six, seven, eight.

145
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:59,300
All right. That's all for today's practice.

146
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:02,000
<i>Thank you.</i>

147
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,600
Lin Shiyin.

148
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,200
Stay.

149
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,900
<i>[Dance Room]</i>

150
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:17,200
What are you looking at?

151
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,200
Shiyin is in there.

152
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:41,800
You must be exhausted.

153
00:10:43,870 --> 00:10:45,150
It's been hard on you.

154
00:10:45,150 --> 00:10:48,580
I just realized that you have no talent at all.

155
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:54,440
But it's good that you are willing to work hard for it.

156
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:58,390
Sir, am I really that bad?

157
00:10:58,390 --> 00:11:00,800
What do you want to hear, the truth or something else?

158
00:11:02,240 --> 00:11:05,500
I always thought I was pretty good.

159
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:07,650
People tend to have the wrong impression

160
00:11:07,650 --> 00:11:09,630
and think they're different from others.

161
00:11:09,630 --> 00:11:11,450
But the truth is...

162
00:11:13,030 --> 00:11:17,640
there's only one way for the untalented to improve themselves.

163
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:21,370
- What is it?
- Be obedient.

164
00:11:22,450 --> 00:11:25,250
- But I...
- It upset me when you questioned me earlier.

165
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:28,250
You know what? I was the one who chose you from an ocean of crowds.

166
00:11:28,250 --> 00:11:31,280
You should know that you don't have what it takes to be the main dancer.

167
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:33,910
I discovered you and guided you.

168
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:36,000
That's how you became the focus.

169
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,500
But you challenged me in public.

170
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:40,240
Was that right of you?

171
00:11:42,630 --> 00:11:44,610
I'm sorry, sir.

172
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:48,640
I forgive you.

173
00:11:49,790 --> 00:11:51,223
Here.

174
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:59,773
Right now, look at yourself.

175
00:11:59,773 --> 00:12:01,650
Keep dancing.

176
00:12:01,650 --> 00:12:03,750
Dance until there are no more flaws.

177
00:12:03,750 --> 00:12:05,283
All right?

178
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:09,060
I believe in you.

179
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:36,000
Seriously?

180
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,430
See? Xue doesn't buy that.

181
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:43,760
Juliet.

182
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:48,800
You're the beautiful sun, my soul mate, and my love.

183
00:12:49,550 --> 00:12:53,970
Your eyes shine so brightly in space

184
00:12:53,970 --> 00:12:56,900
that the birds sing their song as they mistakenly

185
00:12:56,900 --> 00:12:59,200
think the night is over.

186
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,950
How wonderful your posture is?

187
00:13:02,670 --> 00:13:05,330
How I wish I was a glove on your hand

188
00:13:05,330 --> 00:13:08,730
so I could kiss your fragrant hand.

189
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:32,150
Why are you here?

190
00:13:32,150 --> 00:13:34,950
I just happened to be passing by.

191
00:13:56,030 --> 00:13:58,540
School's over. Stop practicing.

192
00:13:59,630 --> 00:14:02,890
That teacher was wrong. Don't believe his words.

193
00:14:06,440 --> 00:14:09,350
What do you know? He's an artist.

194
00:14:09,350 --> 00:14:11,140
I think he is an incompetent guy.

195
00:14:11,140 --> 00:14:13,750
He gets his sense of presence by hurting others.

196
00:14:13,750 --> 00:14:15,200
Don't you say that!

197
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,840
Shiyin, don't trust him.

198
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:18,390
You're not what he said you were.

199
00:14:18,390 --> 00:14:20,330
Well, I believe him.

200
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:24,940
Stay out of my business!

201
00:14:40,130 --> 00:14:44,030
I admit that my performance was kind of exaggerated.

202
00:14:44,030 --> 00:14:47,550
But that's my understanding of the character, Aotian.

203
00:14:51,390 --> 00:14:55,250
I admit that I kind of forgot my lines.

204
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:58,660
But a good actor never has to stick to the screenplay.

205
00:14:59,790 --> 00:15:01,323
Maybe I could go...

206
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:05,480
talk to Ms. Miao and tell her to give us another chance?

207
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:07,030
No need for that.

208
00:15:10,020 --> 00:15:12,160
If that's the case,

209
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:16,070
let's eat something nice to cool down.

210
00:15:16,550 --> 00:15:18,550
Unreliable.

211
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:21,300
Not only is Zhang Qi unreliable, but you as well, Sunian!

212
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:23,640
Why am I unreliable?

213
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:27,170
Just keep your mouth shut.

214
00:15:27,170 --> 00:15:28,550
Had I known, I wouldn't have asked you to perform.

215
00:15:28,550 --> 00:15:30,461
It would have been better if I'd spent 10 yuan to get the sundry shop's owner

216
00:15:30,461 --> 00:15:32,690
- to perform instead of you two!
- Well, 10 yuan isn't enough.

217
00:15:32,690 --> 00:15:34,470
I asked him to play my dad once. His acting was terrible.

218
00:15:34,470 --> 00:15:37,670
I don't want to talk to you! Move!

219
00:15:45,540 --> 00:15:46,860
It's just a cultural performance.

220
00:15:46,860 --> 00:15:48,810
Does she have to be so mad?

221
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,590
Shao Xue.

222
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:58,220
Hi. I'm Wang Haoran.

223
00:15:58,220 --> 00:15:59,800
The Little Li Flying Dagger?

224
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:01,010
What?

225
00:16:01,010 --> 00:16:03,470
Nothing, I know who you are.

226
00:16:04,320 --> 00:16:07,681
Sure enough. All the girls in this school know me.

227
00:16:09,270 --> 00:16:11,510
I think it's a shame that your stage play didn't go as planned.

228
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:13,390
Right? I thought the same, too!

229
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:15,510
- The actors didn't put any effort into it.
- I thought the same, too!

230
00:16:15,510 --> 00:16:17,621
- I'm thinking of giving you a chance.
- I thought...

231
00:16:17,621 --> 00:16:19,103
What?

232
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:23,020
As the president of the Drama Club,

233
00:16:23,020 --> 00:16:25,290
I'd like to invite you to join the club.

234
00:16:25,290 --> 00:16:27,870
I don't think that's necessary.

235
00:16:27,870 --> 00:16:29,240
Don't feel unworthy of it.

236
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:31,000
If I think you can, you can.

237
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,533
Xue.

238
00:16:34,270 --> 00:16:37,600
Isn't this the warrior who wanted to die so badly?

239
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,480
Isn't this Romeo?

240
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,060
- Why are you here?
- Xue.

241
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:42,900
Pizza Hut just launched a new flavor. Let's try it out.

242
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:44,323
I'm not going.

243
00:16:44,323 --> 00:16:45,720
Come on, Xue.

244
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:48,140
We can discuss the acting.

245
00:16:49,750 --> 00:16:51,630
What's going on?

246
00:16:51,630 --> 00:16:53,280
Just a lunatic.

247
00:16:57,670 --> 00:16:59,560
Sorry, I'm late.

248
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,950
I just sent Shiyin home.

249
00:17:03,970 --> 00:17:06,680
It's okay. There's not a lot of stock today.

250
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:09,340
It's fine. I'll take care of the rest. You can take a break.

251
00:17:09,340 --> 00:17:10,620
It's all right.

252
00:17:10,620 --> 00:17:13,050
I have nothing to do anyway.

253
00:17:14,790 --> 00:17:16,323
Wu Huan!

254
00:17:16,323 --> 00:17:19,140
Here. The packaging was damaged, and it fell out.

255
00:17:19,140 --> 00:17:22,440
It looks just like you. You can have it.

256
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:25,180
- Thank you, sir.
- Don't mention it.

257
00:17:29,510 --> 00:17:31,790
Do you like it? You can take it.

258
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:34,280
No. It's a gift for you.

259
00:17:34,280 --> 00:17:35,680
Why would a guy want this?

260
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,113
You can have it.

261
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:04,420
Can't you see that you're unwanted here?

262
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:06,480
I don't think so.

263
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:08,480
Who invited you here?

264
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:11,590
If I don't come, she's not going to come either.

265
00:18:11,590 --> 00:18:13,640
Where does your confidence come from?

266
00:18:14,590 --> 00:18:16,123
Anywhere.

267
00:18:18,590 --> 00:18:20,810
Aren't you eating?

268
00:18:20,810 --> 00:18:22,130
I'm trying to keep fit.

269
00:18:22,130 --> 00:18:23,790
Why are you here then?

270
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:27,910
I've come to experience the taste of junk to know how healthy I am.

271
00:18:27,910 --> 00:18:30,040
Junk.

272
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:35,350
But seeing how much you enjoyed it, I feel like taking a bite too.

273
00:18:35,350 --> 00:18:37,340
Buy it yourself.

274
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,650
It's just one piece. Do you have to do this?

275
00:18:40,650 --> 00:18:43,480
It's not too late for you to leave now.

276
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,070
But that's not what Xue wants.

277
00:18:45,070 --> 00:18:47,440
Who are you to call her Xue?

278
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:50,480
I'm already feeling annoyed, and you won't give me a break.

279
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:52,240
Enjoy yourselves.

280
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:55,283
Sit down!

281
00:19:05,750 --> 00:19:08,270
Your hostility towards me is pretty obvious.

282
00:19:08,270 --> 00:19:10,900
No hostility. We just don't want to be friends with you.

283
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:12,110
But that's not what Shao Xue thinks.

284
00:19:12,110 --> 00:19:14,150
You're overthinking it.

285
00:19:23,890 --> 00:19:25,580
Interesting.

286
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:52,590
<i>Sunian, you wanted to see me?</i>

287
00:19:53,130 --> 00:19:54,970
<i>Sunian!</i>

288
00:19:55,870 --> 00:19:58,731
<i>Sunian, how did you find this place?</i>

289
00:19:58,731 --> 00:20:01,440
<i>Sunian, I was afraid you'd make fun of me.</i>

290
00:20:01,440 --> 00:20:03,170
<i>I got everything! Don't worry. Let's go home!</i>

291
00:20:03,170 --> 00:20:05,270
<i>Sunian.</i>

292
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:07,110
<i>Sunian, you're so lame.</i>

293
00:20:07,110 --> 00:20:09,310
<i>Sunian.</i>

294
00:20:09,310 --> 00:20:11,670
<i>As expected of my lead actor.</i>

295
00:20:11,670 --> 00:20:13,641
<i>Sunian can always think of some wonderful ideas.</i>

296
00:20:13,641 --> 00:20:16,051
<i>You'll always be the Sunian that I know.</i>

297
00:20:16,051 --> 00:20:18,050
<i>Sunian!</i>

298
00:20:22,830 --> 00:20:24,750
- Dad.
- Your milk.

299
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,733
Dad.

300
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:33,110
Back then, how did you know?

301
00:20:34,350 --> 00:20:35,840
Know what?

302
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:37,900
How do you know...

303
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:40,830
if you like women?

304
00:20:44,790 --> 00:20:47,780
- I...
<i>- Zheng, come and help me out!</i>

305
00:20:47,780 --> 00:20:49,760
Coming!

306
00:20:51,350 --> 00:20:53,070
This woman.

307
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:56,210
This woman...

308
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:59,590
This woman is your mom.

309
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:02,073
She...

310
00:21:02,720 --> 00:21:03,900
Right.

311
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:05,533
Yes.

312
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:09,200
I'm feeling a little sleepy.

313
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:11,270
Rest earlier, Dad.

314
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:24,310
I think if you like someone,

315
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:26,450
that feeling lasts for a lifetime.

316
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:31,350
<i>Zheng, what are you doing? Hurry up!</i>

317
00:22:01,510 --> 00:22:03,830
<i>Ms. Miao. Zhang Qi has friends.</i>

318
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:05,860
<i>I'm his friend.</i>

319
00:22:07,170 --> 00:22:09,060
<i>Failure is the mother of success. Don't you know that?</i>

320
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:10,750
<i>I'll buy you noodles. How about that?</i>

321
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:12,483
<i>How do I look?</i>

322
00:22:23,730 --> 00:22:25,380
Why are you laughing?

323
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:26,920
Why are you here?

324
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:29,451
Nonsense! Can't I come back to my own house?

325
00:22:29,451 --> 00:22:31,340
Didn't you say you were working overtime and wouldn't come home tonight?

326
00:22:31,340 --> 00:22:34,070
Says who?

327
00:22:35,540 --> 00:22:39,780
You're blushing. Is there a little secret?

328
00:22:39,780 --> 00:22:41,510
- Are you dating someone?
- No.

329
00:22:41,510 --> 00:22:43,680
Tell me. Is she pretty?

330
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:46,010
- Just go home and sleep!
- Go home and sleep?

331
00:22:46,010 --> 00:22:47,670
What are you talking about? This is our home.

332
00:22:47,670 --> 00:22:51,110
Where else should I go, you punk?

333
00:22:51,110 --> 00:22:53,190
You have a little secret.

334
00:22:53,190 --> 00:22:55,110
Get to bed now.

335
00:23:01,620 --> 00:23:03,360
<i>[Teachers' Office]</i>

336
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:07,253
Morning.

337
00:23:07,253 --> 00:23:09,043
Good morning.

338
00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:18,300
Xue, I'm sorry about yesterday.

339
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:21,090
It was my fault. I had stage fright.

340
00:23:21,090 --> 00:23:24,240
It's not your fault. You didn't do it on purpose.
<i>[A Pocket New English-Chinese Dictionary]</i>

341
00:23:24,240 --> 00:23:26,100
But those two screwed it up on purpose.

342
00:23:26,100 --> 00:23:28,170
Given their performances, there was no way we'd pass.

343
00:23:28,170 --> 00:23:30,690
They... perhaps, it's because they hardly know me.

344
00:23:30,690 --> 00:23:34,140
Why don't I ask Ms. Miao to make you the lead actress and give us another chance to perform?

345
00:23:34,140 --> 00:23:35,620
It'll surely be great.

346
00:23:35,620 --> 00:23:38,650
Shao Xue, someone's looking for you.

347
00:23:39,590 --> 00:23:41,930
I'll talk to you later.

348
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,793
What's up?

349
00:23:53,780 --> 00:23:55,960
I went to see Ms. Miao yesterday.

350
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:59,690
She's willing to give us another chance.

351
00:23:59,690 --> 00:24:01,350
How's that possible?

352
00:24:01,350 --> 00:24:02,900
You don't believe me?

353
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:04,780
What did you do?

354
00:24:06,580 --> 00:24:10,910
I had a sincere conversation with her.

355
00:24:16,410 --> 00:24:18,343
<i>Ms. Miao.</i>

356
00:24:18,343 --> 00:24:19,900
<i>Yes?</i>

357
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:22,150
<i>I have a favor to ask of you.</i>

358
00:24:24,830 --> 00:24:27,070
<i>What are you doing?</i>

359
00:24:27,070 --> 00:24:28,380
For real?

360
00:24:28,380 --> 00:24:30,480
The talented are generally bold.

361
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:35,750
<i>Our parents dedicated great efforts to making this sword and outfit.</i>

362
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:39,520
<i>Please take their efforts into consideration</i>

363
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:43,930
<i>and give us another chance.</i>

364
00:24:43,930 --> 00:24:47,010
Sunian, you're awesome!

365
00:24:48,590 --> 00:24:50,200
We've been given another chance now.

366
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:52,480
But there's something you need to know.

367
00:24:52,480 --> 00:24:54,883
- How to teach you two?
- Of course not.

368
00:24:54,883 --> 00:24:57,120
It's Tang Ya's stage fright.

369
00:24:57,120 --> 00:25:00,100
Let's make you the lead actress. That's way safer.

370
00:25:00,100 --> 00:25:03,690
Sunian, have you forgotten why I wanted to direct a play?

371
00:25:03,690 --> 00:25:05,200
You dream to be a director.

372
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:06,540
That was the case at first.

373
00:25:06,540 --> 00:25:09,620
But right now, I want to help Tang Ya find her confidence

374
00:25:09,620 --> 00:25:12,440
- and let her know how great she is.
- Understood.

375
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:15,190
- Understood
- Will you help us?

376
00:25:15,190 --> 00:25:16,440
I'll do my best.

377
00:25:16,440 --> 00:25:17,790
Sunian, you're the best.

378
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:19,740
I'll get back to class.

379
00:25:19,740 --> 00:25:21,183
Bye.

380
00:25:21,750 --> 00:25:23,283
Bye.

